{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/guide/creating-a-userscript/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Violentmonkey"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"94fdf326-1022-52ad-a3ef-40a6b8f96b3e","html":"<p>Assuming you already know what a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Userscript\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">userscript</a> is, we will talk about how to create your own userscript here.</p>\n<p>With the help of a userscript manager, such as Violentmonkey, you can easily create your own script.</p>\n<h2 id=\"create-a-userscript-for-the-active-tab\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#create-a-userscript-for-the-active-tab\" aria-label=\"create a userscript for the active tab permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Create a userscript for the active tab</h2>\n<p>First make sure you have <a href=\"/get-it/\">Violentmonkey</a> installed.</p>\n<p>Then you'll find a monkey icon on the toolbar of your browser.</p>\n<p>Click on the toolbar icon, and then click on the Plus icon to create a new script for the site of the active tab.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 333px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/80726b39919f5a205b7af42b156d5bc9/24c7e/easy-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/80726b39919f5a205b7af42b156d5bc9/8e964/easy-1.webp 150w,\n/static/80726b39919f5a205b7af42b156d5bc9/c85cb/easy-1.webp 300w,\n/static/80726b39919f5a205b7af42b156d5bc9/f885a/easy-1.webp 333w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 333px) 100vw, 333px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/80726b39919f5a205b7af42b156d5bc9/8a4e8/easy-1.png 150w,\n/static/80726b39919f5a205b7af42b156d5bc9/5a46d/easy-1.png 300w,\n/static/80726b39919f5a205b7af42b156d5bc9/24c7e/easy-1.png 333w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 333px) 100vw, 333px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/80726b39919f5a205b7af42b156d5bc9/24c7e/easy-1.png\"\n          alt=\"easy 1\"\n          title=\"easy 1\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"what-makes-up-a-userscript\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#what-makes-up-a-userscript\" aria-label=\"what makes up a userscript permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What makes up a userscript</h2>\n<p>A userscript consists of two parts: the metadata and your program.</p>\n<p>The metadata declares the basic information of a script:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>descriptive fields, like name, description, author, etc.;</li>\n<li>APIs and permissions, like in which URLs the script is allowed to run;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For more details, see <a href=\"/api/metadata-block/\">Metadata Block</a> and <a href=\"/api/gm/\">GM functions</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token comment\">// ==UserScript==</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// @name        New script</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// @namespace   Violentmonkey Scripts</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// @match       *://*/*</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// @grant       none</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// @version     1.0</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// @author      -</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// @description 3/8/2020, 8:42:28 PM</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// ==/UserScript==</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The rest part of the code runs in target webpages as usual JavaScript assets.</p>\n<h2 id=\"userscript-code\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#userscript-code\" aria-label=\"userscript code permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Userscript code</h2>\n<p>Please note that the code executes directly in the browser, so the syntax in this script must be supported by the browser natively.</p>\n<p>For example, ESNext features that are not supported by the browser will fail as <code class=\"language-text\">SyntaxError</code>.</p>\n<p>Modern browsers like Chrome, Firefox, Edge support most of ES 6 features, so it is safe to use most of them if you are not targetting last century users.</p>\n<p>However there are exceptions. For example ES modules won't work in userscripts because they are supposed to inject into webpage as single-file scripts.</p>\n<p>If you want to write userscripts with some awesome features that are not supported by browsers yet or won't be supported, such as ES modules, CSS modules, please check out <a href=\"../using-modern-syntax/\">How to use modern syntax in a userscript</a>.</p>","fields":{"tagSlugs":null,"type":"pages"},"frontmatter":{"title":"How to create a userscript","tags":null,"date":"2020-03-08 18:33:51+0800","sidebar":{"match":"/guide/","order":0}},"tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/guide/creating-a-userscript/#create-a-userscript-for-the-active-tab\">Create a userscript for the active tab</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/guide/creating-a-userscript/#what-makes-up-a-userscript\">What makes up a userscript</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/guide/creating-a-userscript/#userscript-code\">Userscript code</a></li>\n</ul>"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/guide/creating-a-userscript/","type":"pages"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1878747374","2176765690","2344890832","3202921338","3365866253"]}